The terms social network and social media are used interchangeably now, but they shouldnâ€™t be. A social network is an idle, inactive system -- a Rolodex of contacts, a notebook of sales targets, a yearbook of possible soul mates. But social media is active -- hyperactive, really -- spewing material across those networks instead of leaving them alone until needed.

